cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with media streaming over the internet and proposes a swarming-based approach to leverage client heterogeneity. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with live streaming of media content. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a peer-to-peer (P2P) approach for content delivery. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a mixed strategy for scheduling in a P2P streaming system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper uses mathematical analysis and simulations to evaluate the proposed strategy.
